The paper proposes a system model that utilizes temporal convolutions with both long term and short term time dependencies to accurately estimate the remaining useful life (RUL) of industrial machinery. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of neural networks for RUL estimation suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. The focus on industrial machinery and system modeling suggests that the paper may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the use of sensor values and data augmentation suggests that the paper may also belong to the computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
